		{"id":"52689c10076f923a","x":1260,"y":1040,"width":980,"height":690,"color":"4","type":"text","text":"\n#### Making custom file in `rsyslog.conf` file\n```\n1. vim /etc/rsyslog.conf\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ This command open the rsyslog.conf file in vi editor now let's make selector and action\n\nentry this in rsyslog.conf file ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡\n\nlocal4.crit               /var/log/critandabove\nlocal4.=crit              /var/log/crit\nlocal4.*                  /var/log/alllocal4logs\n\n2. systemctl restart rsyslog.service\n\n```\n\n```\n1. logger -p local4.debug \"14 debug\"\n2. logger -p local4.crit \"14 critical\"\n3. logger -p local4.emerg \"14 emergency\"\n\n*** logger command is used to put the log intentionally in repective logger file ***\n\nAlso\nlocal4 is facility part in selector and .dubug or .crit is the priority part in selector\nAll this log is genereated under /var/log/critandabove, /var/log/crit, /var/log/alllocal4logs file\n\n```\n\n"},
